raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.3.0' %}

{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-spscomps
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/spsComps_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/spsComps/spsComps_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 1d7e359ef62ffb543d0d0221130be1788f9654073599bf526fb52ffd7a348e0b

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  skip: true  # [r_base == "3.6"]
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

# Suggests: testthat, shinyjqui, spsUtil (>= 0.1.2)
requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-assertthat
    - r-crayon
    - r-glue >=1.4.0
    - r-htmltools
    - r-magrittr
    - r-shiny >=1.5.0
    - r-shinyace
    - r-shinytoastr
    - r-stringr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-assertthat
    - r-crayon
    - r-glue >=1.4.0
    - r-htmltools
    - r-magrittr
    - r-shiny >=1.5.0
    - r-shinyace
    - r-shinytoastr
    - r-stringr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('spsComps')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('spsComps')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/lz100/spsComps
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  summary: The systemPipeShiny (SPS) framework comes with many UI and server components. However,
    installing the whole framework is heavy and takes some time. If you would like to
    use UI and server components from SPS in your own Shiny apps, do not hesitate to
    try this package.

  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
